{"TopicId":135527,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Next generation thermometer bearing/hinge 1.1 compatable","CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-31T15:53:06Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Torquimedes","CreatedById":137645,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-29T23:10:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222992842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135527\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490113410\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2017 at 11:23 AM, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, also, try using an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E block instead of an antenna if it\u0027s a high stress system. They tend to be more reliable for high weight, high stress mechanisms.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\nAs an example:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rcUxrPZ.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/rcUxrPZ.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\nI tweaked the\u00A0thermo-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ehinge into a ball-and-socket arrangement by angling the thermometers, which resists longitudinal compression of the axle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\nI connected wings, dockingports\u00A0and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E-levers to the central cubic strut for movable wings on these craft. \u00A0There\u0027s a motion diagram\u00A0to see how they work in 4D.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/158378-stock-x-wings-with-moving-s-foils-and-repulsorlift-image-heavy/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-30T16:33:55Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2017 04:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Torquimedes\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aphobius","CreatedById":79391,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-10T07:37:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to check this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/158977-stock-triple-axis-tourbillon-clock/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klond","CreatedById":38787,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-10T15:38:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223016123\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135527\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491809865\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279391\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aphobius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Aphobius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to check this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/158977-stock-triple-axis-tourbillon-clock/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I\u0027m glad you crossposted -\u00A0I think I would have missed it otherwise.\u00A0 Amazing!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-10T15:38:50Z\u0022 title=\u002204/10/2017 03:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by klond\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aphobius","CreatedById":79391,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-30T12:23:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, I\u0027m trying to make a new clock, but I need some help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a reaction wheel that can roll freely by using a thermometer hinge. But I use if for some kind of escapement and when the teeth (antennas that I\u0027ve placed on it) hit something, the whole thing is bouncing a few times before stopping.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone has any ideas how I could add some friction to it? (hopefully that will\u00A0stop the bouncing)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried to place thermometers around the reaction wheel, if I place them radially, the friction is not smooth, if I place them on the flat faces of the reaction wheel, I don\u0027t get any friction at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve also tried to place the thermometers of the hinge closer together, but that makes the hinge unstable and doesn\u0027t seem to add any friction at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought about using landing gears, but they are too big and they don\u0027t fit well inside the whole mechanism.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: I\u0027ve solved the bouncing by making some kind of\u00A0ratchet. Added an antenna that slows down the gear before the correct position and after that blocks it from rotating back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill, if anyone has an idea of how we can add constant friction to the thermometer hinge, it might be useful for other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-30T13:23:13Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2017 01:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Aphobius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}